Vosk is an offline open source speech recognition toolkit. 
Vosk works for both small devices like Raspberry Pi and big clusters. 

    1. Get the python module for Vosk, pip install vosk 

    2. Go to Alpha Cepheimodels, https://alphacephei.com/vosk/models download the vosk-model-small-en-us-0.15 

    3. Add model to Lib > SitePackages > same directory where other Python libraries are saved.  

    4. Take the path to this folder and link to the program by replacing the model_path.  

    Extra curiosity, github has extra examples for Vosk and microphone test, https://github.com/alphacep/vosk-api/tree/master/python 